data.name: Cobb Salad Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: A delicious fusion of a classic Cobb salad and a juicy burger, packed with fresh ingredients and bold flavors.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat a grill or skillet over medium-high heat.
In a bowl, season the ground beef with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika. Mix gently and form into 4 patties.
Grill the patties for about 5 minutes on each side, or until they reach your desired doneness.
In the last minute of cooking, place a slice of cheddar cheese on each patty to melt.
Toast the hamburger buns lightly on the grill or in a toaster.

Assemble the burger by placing a lettuce leaf on the bottom bun, followed by the burger patty, bacon, tomato slices, avocado, and chopped hard-boiled eggs. Drizzle ranch dressing on top and close with the top bun.
data.detailedName: Cobb Salad Burger with Ranch Dressing
data.modifiersForBase: Add fresh salad ingredients and ranch dressing
